---
import ModuleLayout from '../../layouts/ModuleLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<ModuleLayout
  title="Processing and End Markets"
  subtitle="Facility upgrades, sorting technology, contamination reduction, and end-market development qualify for reimbursement when tied to California CMCs. See how to evaluate the fit."
  currentPath={`${base}/reimbursement/processing/`}
  prev={{ href: `${base}/reimbursement/collection/`, label: 'Collection Systems' }}
>
  <section class="section">
    <h2>Why this matters to you</h2>
    <p>If you operate a material recovery facility, processing facility, transfer station, or composting facility — or if you're involved in end-market development — SB 54 reimburses eligible investments that improve sorting, processing, and material recovery for covered materials.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Key messages</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Processing and facility investments are eligible for reimbursement — including MRF upgrades, sorting technology, and infrastructure to improve recovery of covered materials (CMCs).</li>
      <li>Funding supports both capital upgrades and operational improvements: equipment, labor, maintenance, and quality control systems tied to processing CMCs.</li>
      <li>Projects must improve material outcomes. Funding is tied to increased recovery, improved quality, and stronger end-market alignment.</li>
      <li>Only technologies that meet SB 54 definitions of recycling are eligible. Disposal-based or energy-generation technologies are excluded.</li>
      <li>Processing may occur both in and outside of California, with accountability tied to California materials and SB 54 outcomes.</li>
      <li>Environmental Justice considerations apply. Projects must assess and mitigate impacts on nearby communities.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Slide deck</h2>
    <p><em>Deck pending — download will be available here.</em></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Video</h2>
    <p><em>Video pending — embed will be available here.</em></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <div class="accordion">
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">What types of processing investments are eligible?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>Equipment upgrades, sorting technology, contamination reduction systems, capacity expansion, system efficiency improvements, and end-market development or innovation.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">Can out-of-state facilities participate?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>Yes. SB 54 recognizes that not all covered materials can be processed in-state. Out-of-state facilities that process California materials can participate, but investments and outcomes must align with SB 54 requirements for recovery, quality, and reporting.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">How are end markets supported?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>Funding can support end-market development and innovation. CAA is working to ensure stable, viable end markets for recyclable materials — a primary concern for processors.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-block">
    <h2>What to do next</h2>

    <div class="cta-block__card">
      <p class="cta-block__label">MRFs, processors, composting, transfer stations</p>
      <p class="cta-block__action"><strong>Start a facility investment conversation with CAA</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-block__card">
      <p class="cta-block__label">Facilities handling mixed material streams</p>
      <p class="cta-block__action"><strong>Download the CMC eligibility worksheet</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-block__card">
      <p class="cta-block__label">Innovators and investors</p>
      <p class="cta-block__action"><strong>Share an end-market or innovation opportunity</strong> — form for new approaches to material processing or system gaps.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-block__card cta-block__card--ready">
      <p class="cta-block__label">Stay ready</p>
      <p class="cta-block__action"><strong>Request a working group invitation</strong> — regional agency roundtable, processor working group.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</ModuleLayout>
